10 B. Only the names of regular employees who have been laid off in
11 accordance with the provisions of R.S. 33:2499 shall be eligible for entry upon the
12 reemployment list. The names of such persons shall be entered upon the
13 reemployment list for the class from which they were laid off in the order in which
14 the lay-offs were made.
15 C. A name placed upon either the reinstatement or the reemployment list
16 shall remain thereon on the list for a period of four years. The board, however, may
17 remove the name of any person who refuses an offer of employment following a
18 certification from either list.
19 D.(1) Except as provided for in Paragraphs (2), and (3), and (4) of this
20 Subsection, names of persons attaining a passing score on a promotion test shall be
21 placed upon the promotion employment list for the class for which they were tested,
22 from highest to lowest, according to their total departmental seniority. The names of
23 persons attaining a passing score on a competitive test shall be placed upon the
24 competitive employment list for the class for which they were tested, from highest
25 to lowest, according to their final test scores.
26 (2)(a) Names The names of persons attaining a passing score on the
27 promotional test in the Lafayette Police Department for the rank of lieutenant or
28 captain, or in the Lake Charles Police Department, shall be placed upon the
29 promotion employment list for the class for which they were tested, from highest to
30 lowest, according to their total promotional seniority in the next lower class. If two
